{"word":"πάρειμι","slug":"πάρειμι","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>πάρειμι</el></b> [<el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:παρά\">παρά</a>, <a class=\"S\" href=\"S:εἰμί\">εἰμί</a></el>] <b>be present <a href='B:510 10:33'>Ac 10:33</a>; <a href='B:510 24:19'>24:19</a>; <a href='B:530 5:3'>1 Cor 5:3</a>; <a href='B:540 10:2'>2 Cor 10:2</a>, <a href='B:540 10:11'>11</a>; <a href='B:540 11:9'>11:9</a>; <a href='B:540 13:2'>13:2</a>, <a href='B:540 13:10'>10</a>; <a href='B:550 4:18'>Gal 4:18</a>, <a href='B:550 4:20'>20</a>; <a href='B:580 1:6'>Col 1:6</a>; <a href='B:730 17:8'>Rv 17:8</a>.</b> As noun <el>τὸ <a class=\"S\" href=\"S:παρόν\">παρόν</a></el> the present <b><a href='B:650 12:11'>Hb 12:11</a>.</b> A nuance, <b>be here/there</b> (like a <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ pf.\">pf.</a> tense in sense of have come), may be expressed in the following: <b><a href='B:470 26:50'>Mt 26:50</a>; <a href='B:490 13:1'>Lk 13:1</a>; <a href='B:500 7:6'>J 7:6</a>; <a href='B:500 11:28'>11:28</a>; <a href='B:510 10:21'>Ac 10:21</a>; <a href='B:510 12:20'>12:20</a>; <a href='B:510 17:6'>17:6</a>; <a href='B:580 1:6'>Col 1:6</a>; <a href='B:680 1:9'>2 Pt 1:9</a>, <a href='B:680 1:12'>12</a>.</b> <el>ἀρϰοῦμενοι τοῖς παροῦσιν</el> being satisfied with what you have at hand (i.e. ‘your possessions’) <b><a href='B:650 13:5'>Hb 13:5</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:παρειμένος\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:παρεῖναι\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}